[{"question":"Is it as dangerous as it seems?","answer":"The outcome still isn\u0027t clear.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":112,"aSentId":113},{"question":"Are there enough people physically to do the job that\u0027s required?","answer":"They have no need to keep more people around than they absolutely need since all of them are soaking up dose.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":131,"aSentId":132},{"question":"How does this disaster compare -- this nuclear plant to something like Chernobyl?","answer":"In Chernobyl, a completely different kind of reactor.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":137,"aSentId":138},{"question":"Without wanting to be doom-laden about this, but what is the worst possible news that you would hear as an expert in this area from that plant?","answer":"Probably that the spent fuel spool is on fire because what would burn there is the metal cladding, and that\u0027s very difficult to put out.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":162,"aSentId":163},{"question":"Why are you confident this is the right way to go?","answer":"Well, the main thing I\u0027ve said, Piers, is not that, but it\u0027s simply that it\u0027s way too early to know.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":171,"aSentId":172},{"question":"We\u0027ve got lots of reactors, many by the sea?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":181,"aSentId":182},{"question":"What\u0027s going to happen if the same thing happens here?","answer":"Piers, it\u0027s an obvious question.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":183,"aSentId":184},{"question":"Quite clearly, this is an ongoing, very serious and dangerous situation, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":193,"aSentId":194},{"question":"What are the lessons that we should learn from what\u0027s happened in regard to America\u0027s plants, do you think?","answer":"Piers, I have no earthly idea.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":198,"aSentId":199},{"question":"Isn\u0027t that the point?","answer":"I think it would -- I think it would be irresponsible to do otherwise.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":210,"aSentId":211},{"question":"Today the energy secretary, Stephen Chu, said that U.S. reactors are designed to withstand hurricanes and tsunamis, but given geologists\u0027 maximum predictions, is that actually enough?","answer":"Well, Piers, I fully agree that there are important lessons to be learned by -- from what has happened at Fukushima.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":234,"aSentId":235},{"question":"As things stand given your knowledge of the nuclear power plants in America, how many of them would you think are able to withstands an earthquake of a magnitude we saw in Japan?","answer":"Well, let\u0027s remember that the reactors in Japan were quite old.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":240,"aSentId":241},{"question":"Wouldn\u0027t that be the first point of thumb that you\u0027d choose?","answer":"Well, the problem with that is that you\u0027d end up building a reactor in a zone that is not subject to earthquakes to withstand an enormous earthquake.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":248,"aSentId":249},{"question":"Finally, Ambassador Ritch, do you think we\u0027re getting the truth out of the Japanese authorities?","answer":"I do, but Piers, lets me make a point.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":260,"aSentId":261},{"question":"For people like most of us who\u0027ve never been anywhere near a tsunami, what is the experience like when it happens?","answer":"The experience is just horrifying because you feel so powerless with the amount of power of the water.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":298,"aSentId":299},{"question":"What is the most effective thing that Americans can do to help?","answer":"On the level of helping children, the best way for them to recover and start healing process is to go back to normalcy, to go back to school, which is safe.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":327,"aSentId":328},{"question":"Do you still have nightmares about it now?","answer":"You always will keep it inside.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":337,"aSentId":338},{"question":"And finally, what would your message be to the people of Japan who are suffering so badly at the moment?","answer":"The message for them is that my heart is breaking looking at what they are going through.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":347,"aSentId":348},{"question":"How are they going to bounce back?","answer":"With time, Piers.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":369,"aSentId":370},{"question":"What will that mean for prices, in terms of their exports going forward?","answer":"Think of it in terms of they are producing and consuming less as a society.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":383,"aSentId":384},{"question":"Is that going to be helpful to Japan, do you think?","answer":"It\u0027s going to be helpful at the margin.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":396,"aSentId":397},{"question":"What is it about the Japanese people that allows them to deal with such catastrophe in what appears to be such a remarkably calm manner?","answer":"Well, I think that we in America -- when we come across a crisis, we tend to come apart at the seams.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":411,"aSentId":412},{"question":"Are they very pro-active at getting things back on their feet again?","answer":"In general, Japanese officials leave one with kind of a sense of horror, I mean, just a difficult grappling with crisis.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":421,"aSentId":422},{"question":"Is that part of their psyche, as well?","answer":"Yes, absolutely.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":439,"aSentId":440},{"question":"Do you still have friends over there?","answer":"Oh, of course.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":448,"aSentId":449},{"question":"Can you talk me through the relative toxicity of each of these?","answer":"Right, there are four different types of radiation, Piers.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":470,"aSentId":471},{"question":"What is the understanding of the levels of radiation coming out of this Japanese plant?","answer":"We\u0027ve been hearing that the levels of radiation are not quite at the level that you would see in order to have acute radiation sickness.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":477,"aSentId":478},{"question":"Tell me this, if they are exposed to very high dosages of radiation, what physically happens to a human being when that happens to them?","answer":"Right, it\u0027s interesting.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":492,"aSentId":493},{"question":"And what are you hearing from Bahrain, where there seems to be an escalation in violence there, as well?","answer":"That\u0027s right.","docId":"110315pmt","qSentId":526,"aSentId":527}]